,{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How Claude's OCR Works"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Technical approach "},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Image → Pixel chunks (x by y) → Tokenized into vectors → Transformer model → Text output"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Images are broken into chunks that are "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"tokenized into arrays of vectors"},{"type":"text","text":" and run through the transformer model "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"just like text"},{"type":"text","text":", using the same model weights (natively multimodal)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Claude 3 models are trained on diverse data formats"},{"type":"text","text":": language, images, charts, diagrams, allowing them to interpret complex visual data."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Best Practices for OCR with Claude"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":4},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. Structured Output Format"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Force JSON output for invoices\nprompt = \"\"\"\nExtract the following fields from this invoice:\n- INVOICE_NUMBER (format: nine-digit number)\n- CUSTOMER_NUMBER (format: alphanumeric)\n- CUSTOMER_NAME\n- VENDOR_NAME\n- INVOICE_AMOUNT (format: currency)\n- INVOICE_DATE (format: YYYY-MM-DD)\n- VENDOR_ADDRESS\n\nReturn in JSON format. If you cannot find a field, return \"UNK\".\n\"\"\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This enforces structured output, making extraction predictable and programmable."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":4},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2. Handle Ambiguity"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":